news.title: GST applicable on voluntary payments made by members to housing societies: AAR
news.para: AAR said that the money received by the society was for the supply of services. GST has a concept called "supply of services," which is used to figure out if a transaction is taxable or not. The AAR cited parts of the Model Bye Laws that say the society can't accept a payment from a transferor or transferee that was made on their own.

news.title: Chandigarh administration may use helpline 112 for illegal constructions
news.para: Presently, people inform the field staff who sometimes reveal the identity of the informer, leading to trouble. A senior official said the issue was recently raised before UT adviser Dharam Pal.

news.title: IIT Delhi develops low cost braces to enhance earthquake resistance in buildings
news.para: According to officials, the braces, for which a patent has also been applied have several advantages, such as all-steel components, on-site fabrication and assembling process, post-earthquake inspection, and easy replacement.

news.title: Police attach Lucknow-based realtor's assets worth Rs 116 crore
news.para: The accused, Paresh Rastogi, has been booked under Gangsters Act. He is named in 82 cases in police stations of Hazratganj, Vibhuti Khand, Gosainganj and others in Lucknow as well as in other districts.

news.title: Over 1.5 lakh houses out of tax net, will send notices to clear dues: Ghaziabad civic body
news.para: After the GMC’s survey, which began last year, the authority will send notices to the house owners, asking them to clear their dues.

news.title: Three years on, no property tax rebate yet for housing societies in Mumbai for treating waste
news.para: The amount of rebate would vary from 5%-15% depending upon how much waste is being treated and processed and also if wastewater is being recycled

news.title: Dharani land portal issues will be resolved: Telangana minister
news.para: Minister Harish Rao along with chief secretary Somesh Kumar and CMO officers held a meeting in Mulugu on Tuesday following the directions of CM K Chandrasekhar Rao.

news.title: UT adviser directs deputy commissioner to rationalise collector rates in Chandigarh
news.para: The adviser said that the DC would review the rates and submit a report after which they would take a call on rationalisation of collector rates.

news.title: Seal 26 highrise commercial buildings sans fire NOC: Gujarat high court
news.para: The high court also ordered the civic body to take action against 1,128 residential buildings and other 259 highrise buildings which are used for commercial and residential purposes.

news.title: Soon, NFT-coded property papers in Kolkata's New Town
news.para: "This way, the document or image becomes exclusive to its owner and nobody is able to fudge it or make a copy," explained Kalyan Kar, an IT expert and startup enthusiast, who is also the vice-president of Sector V Stakeholders' Association.

news.title: Mumbai: ED says builder Sanjay Chhabriaa also diverted Rs 678 crore loan
news.para: ED said Chhabriaa had taken the Rs 678 crore in the name of Flag Industries Pvt Ltd, which was not involved in the Santacruz project, Avenue 54.

news.title: Developer ready for bank guarantee, Ansal Esencia to get power connection soon
news.para: The developer completed the project and received occupation certificate from DTCP without having proper electricity connection and handed over the possession to the homebuyers.

news.title: Gurugram: Takeover of nine colonies today, upkeep in private hands for now
news.para: Officials said the civic body too will have to invite tenders and hire a contractor to take up maintenance work such as sanitation and upkeep of green areas.

news.title: SBI hikes deposit, lending rates
news.para: SBI said interest rates have been raised by 0.20 per cent on domestic term deposits of below Rs 2 crore for select tenors.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance to raise up to Rs 2,000 crore via bonds
news.para: ​The housing finance company, promoted by the city-headquartered Punjab National Bank (PNB), was looking to raise equity capital worth Rs 4,000 crore and struck a deal with joint-venture partner Carlyle Group, among other investors, in May last year.
